{
  "files": [
    {
      "repo": "grafana/grafana",
      "path": "pkg/components/loki/lokihttp/config.go"
    },
    {
      "repo": "grafana/grafana",
      "path": "pkg/components/loki/lokihttp/client.go"
    },
    {
      "repo": "grafana/grafana",
      "path": "pkg/components/loki/lokihttp/fake.go"
    },
    {
      "repo": "grafana/grafana",
      "path": "pkg/components/loki/lokigrpc/config.go"
    },
    {
      "repo": "grafana/grafana",
      "path": "pkg/components/loki/lokigrpc/client.go"
    }
  ],
  "text": "The Loki client retry/timeout logic in grafana/grafana is implemented across both HTTP and gRPC clients under pkg/components/loki/.\n\n**HTTP Client (lokihttp):**\n\n1. **config.go** - Defines the HTTP client configuration struct with BackoffConfig (imported from github.com/grafana/dskit/backoff) and Timeout fields. The BackoffConfig controls exponential backoff behavior for retries.\n\n2. **client.go** - The main HTTP client implementation that implements the Client interface. Key retry/timeout logic includes:\n   - StopNow() method (line 376) that cancels the context to immediately stop retrying HTTP requests\n   - sendBatch() method (line 290) that creates a backoff instance using backoff.New(c.ctx, c.cfg.BackoffConfig) and implements retry logic\n   - send() method (line 330) that applies a Timeout to the context using context.WithTimeout()\n   - Retry logic (lines 301-321) that retries on 429s, 500s, and connection-level errors, using backoff.Wait() to delay between retries and checking backoff.Ongoing() before retrying\n   - The HTTP client timeout is set at line 175: c.client.Timeout = cfg.Timeout\n\n3. **fake.go** - The test fake/stub client implementation that implements the Client interface with a StopNow() method (line 39) for testing purposes.\n\n**gRPC Client (lokigrpc):**\n\n1. **config.go** - Defines the gRPC client configuration struct with Retries (uint) and Timeout (time.Duration) fields.\n\n2. **client.go** - The gRPC client implementation that handles retry and timeout configuration:\n   - grpcRetryOption() method (line 82) that uses grpcretry.UnaryClientInterceptor with grpcretry.WithMax(c.cfg.Retries) to configure the maximum number of retries\n   - timeoutCtx() method (line 90) that applies the Timeout configuration using context.WithTimeout() when Timeout > 0\n   - The Write() method uses timeoutCtx() to create a context with timeout before pushing requests\n\nAll five files work together to provide comprehensive retry and timeout configuration for Loki log ingestion, with the HTTP client using exponential backoff via BackoffConfig and the gRPC client using gRPC middleware interceptors."
}

